snippet: A spokesman said that the union extracted promises from management that, as workers retire or leave, no more than 14 jobs will be outsourced.
abstract: Workers at ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach return to work after eight-day strike that paralyzed nation’s busiest shipping complex; spokesman for International Longshore and Warehouse Union says that it extracted promises from management about limits on job outsourcing.
lead_paragraph: A spokesman said that the union extracted promises from management that, as workers retire or leave, no more than 14 jobs will be outsourced.

headline.seo: Port Clerks Claim Win on Jobs as Los Angeles Strike Ends
headline.main: Shipping Strike in Los Angeles Ends
